## 📁 Project Structure

```
d:\NoteGo_RAG\
├── app.py                  # Main Streamlit app — UI, chat, file upload
├── requirements.txt        # All Python dependencies
├── README.md               # Project documentation
├── src/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── file_parser.py      # Functions to extract text from PDF, DOCX, PPT
│   ├── chunker.py          # Text splitting with overlap
│   ├── embeddings.py       # Wrapper around Ollama's nomic-embed-text
│   ├── vector_store.py     # ChromaDB create/query/add operations
│   └── rag_chain.py        # LangChain RAG pipeline — ties everything together
├── data/
│   └── uploads/            # Temporarily stores uploaded files
└── chroma_db/              # ChromaDB's persistent storage (auto-created)
```

---

## 📈 Improvement Roadmap

### Phase 1 — MVP *(what we build first)*
Simple file upload + text extraction + chunking + vector search + LLM Q&A with source references.

### Phase 2 — Better Accuracy
- **Hybrid Search:** Combine semantic search with BM25 keyword search so that exact terms like formula names or acronyms are not missed.
- **Re-ranking:** After retrieving the top 10 chunks, use a cross-encoder model to re-score and pick the truly best 5. This dramatically improves answer quality.
- **Table Extraction:** Properly parse tables from PDFs and DOCX files instead of just extracting raw text (which often scrambles table data).
- **OCR Support:** Use Tesseract to extract text from scanned/image-based PDFs.

### Phase 3 — Google Classroom Integration & Multi-User
- **Google Classroom API:** Auto-fetch all course materials from a Google Classroom course instead of manual upload.
- **Multi-course Support:** Separate vector stores per course so answers don't mix between subjects.
- **Chat History:** Remember previous questions in the session so students can ask follow-ups like "explain that in simpler words."
- **Quiz Generation:** Use the indexed notes to auto-generate MCQs and short-answer questions for revision.

### Phase 4 — Production Polish
- **Streaming Responses:** Show the answer token by token as it's generated for better UX.
- **Citation Highlighting:** Link each sentence of the answer to the exact source page/slide.
- **Cloud Deployment:** Deploy on a VM so any student can access it via a URL.
- **Analytics Dashboard:** Track which topics students ask about most to help teachers identify weak areas.

---

## ⚡ Quick Start Commands

```bash
# 1. Install Ollama from https://ollama.com/download
# 2. Pull models
ollama pull mistral
ollama pull nomic-embed-text

# 3. Set up Python environment
cd d:\NoteGo_RAG
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate

# 4. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 5. Run the app
streamlit run app.py
```
